welcome_screens.title:
Hello, welcome to SF Service Guide's resource guide for *Affordable Housing*. Our goal is to help you find the resources that you need.

To do that, we'll have to ask a few questions to see what resources you are eligible for. We will not ask for any personal information like name or phone number, and all responses will remain confidential.

Here are ShelterTech's best recommendations for you:

*Step 1:* Sign up for Affordable Housing Rental Workshops below:

*HomeownershipSF*
_Address:_ Depends on the workshop (see link below)
_Services_: Rental Preparedness Workshops
_Languages Served_: English and Spanish
_Find Workshops Here:_ *https://homeownershipsf.org/events/category/workshops/rental-workshops/*

*Step 2:* We also recommend that you create a DAHLIA account if you have not already. DAHLIA will allow you to find affordable rental housing that you might be eligible for. To create an account, follow [*this link*](https://housing.sfgov.org/) to get started. 

*Please note:* that there are minimum income requirements for DAHLIA rental listings. You will have a higher chance of qualifying for DAHLIA rental opportunities if you meet one or more of the following lottery preferences [*found here*](https://sfmohcd.org/lottery-preference-programs).

*Step 3:* If you are looking for more resources, in addition to the links above, you can access our SF Service Guide database for Affordable Housing resources by following [*this link*](https://sfserviceguide.org/search?query=rental+workshops).

Here are ShelterTech's best recommendations for you:

*Step 1:* DAHLIA is a San Francisco Housing Portal sponsored by the SF Mayor's Office that helps you find affordable rental housing. If you don't have an account already, you can follow [*this link*](https://housing.sfgov.org/) to get started. 

*Please note:* that there are minimum income requirements for DAHLIA rental listings. You will have a higher chance of qualifying for DAHLIA rental opportunities if you meet one or more of the following lottery preferences [*found here*](https://sfmohcd.org/lottery-preference-programs).

*Step 2:* Make sure you check your email regularly (if you have one) in order to see new housing opportunities. Start your rental housing search here: *https://housing.sfgov.org/listings/for-rent*.

*Step 3:* Check out additional housing resources here: *https://housing.sfgov.org/additional-resources*.

*Step 4:* If you are looking for more resources, in addition to the links above, please follow this link to access our SF Service Guide database for Affordable Housing resources by following [*this link*](https://sfserviceguide.org/search?query=affordable+housing).

Here are ShelterTech's best recommendations for you:

*Home Buyer Education Requirements Effective August 1, 2019:*

To apply for a First Time Home buyer program in San Francisco, adult applicants age 18 and older must complete 10 hours of first-time home buyer education and receive their First Time Home Buyer Certificate: 

*Step 1:* Complete MOHCD's 2 hour long Home Buyer Program Orientation. You can see a list of upcoming events [*here*](https://homeownershipsf.org/events/category/workshops/home-buyers-orientation/).

*Step 2*: Complete 6 hours of First Time Home Buyer (FTHB) Workshop(s) at one of the five approved agencies (may be taken as series at the SF LGBT Center or online through SFHDC). You can see a list of these in-person workshops [*here*](https://homeownershipsf.org/events/category/workshops/home-buyers-workshops/) and online workshops [*here*](https://www.ehomeamerica.org/sfhdc)*.*

*Step 3:* Attend a 2 hour Individual Counseling Session at the *same* agency as FTHB workshop. You will receive your Buyer Verification form after completing at the end of this counseling session.

*Step 4:* If you are looking for more resources, in addition to the links above, please follow this link to access our SF Service Guide database for Affordable Housing resources by following [*this link*](https://sfserviceguide.org/search?query=affordable+housing).
